betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Welcome to your fun greg journey.
The early game of this modpack will drag, thats a fun word through botania to produce ores using magic before greg.
Craft some Floral Fertilizer from them Living Roots, You will need this to progress more in Botania.
Chop a tree. If you find that a tree doesn't grow instantly pressing the shift key quickly with make a tree grow faster.
Now you have Floral Fertilizer you can click it on the dirt platform you have (I Hope you do) to produce Mystical Flowers. For this quest I task you with collecting 2 Mystical White Flowers.
The Pure daisy is essential to get closer to making your first ores.
To produce your first mana you need an Endoflame Flower from botania, It can run on any furnace fuel you want. The fuel you can use Is a trade secret but i'm sure you can figure it out :)
So to get cobblestone in this, before you get lava is to hold your shift key and click with your right mouse button (Keybinds may vary). This in tern will give you pebbles.

Now you have cobblestone and mystical flowers you can now craft a Petal Apothecary.
I suggest you keep at least 1 seed from this quest so you can plant more.
Now you have a pure daisy you can now make living rock and living wood.
betterquesting:10.name:8: Its Alive, I mean, 96% well done Jesse.

betterquesting:10.desc:8: What!?! Your surprized this recipe is not somthing crazy. Now that sounds increadibly silly :)
To actually Fill your Petal Apothecary you will need water. to get water for now you need cyan and blue powder mixed with a bowl. yes you can use that to fill the Petal Apothecary.

Mana Spreader: Extracts mana from mana generating flowers.
Mana Pool: Stores Mana for later use, Aim Mana Spreader at teh Mana Pool.
Wand of the Forest: Needed to rotate Mana Spreader and bind Flowers to Spreaders.
You have made it this far, Well done. You now need to craft an orchid to start generating ores. Ill give you a pickaxe to mine the ores but i suggest making one for the future :)
You can now Collect ores! To make Mana Steel you will need to collect some Copper and Tin Ore for Bronze and make a Mortar to grind Ingots into dusts.
Stone is needed to produce ores with the Orechid, Hense the need for a furnace.
Bronze is going to be used a lot in this chapter. I hope you can generate ores quickly enough.
Now you can make your first set of tools. Flint will have to do, Later on you will get some better materials to make tools out of :D
This Mortar is the next step in progression. required for large amounts of bronze and to craft your very first tools.
By Placing Cobblestone next to the Pure Daisy, You can produce gravel. Gravel will be used to make your first mortar.
Cobaltite Vein Contains 4 main ores Cobalt, Cobaltite, Realgar and Sulfur. All important elements for creating Electronic Circuits.
All the other ores you can produce from the orchid can be found in jei.
The Forge Hammer can create plates at a ratio of 1.5 ingots to 1 plate instead of 2 ingots to 1 plate.
The Compressor will be used to make certain Plates from Dusts and more importently produce Firebricks From Firebrick Dust.
The Steam Alloy Smelter lets you combine metals Like Tin and Copper to produce Bronze. It can also be used to make other materials like Rubber and Iron
The Extrator will be your gateway into producing Rubber from Slimonds or Sticky Resin.
If you craft some Coarse Dirt and drop it into a Mana Pool with a bit of mana, It will give you dirt. Infinite Dirt anyone?
With The macerator you can now produce double the ore output. In my opinion this is essental for you since ores come from the Orchid.
Steam Furnace allows you to smelt things for Steam instead of furnace fuels.
This Type of Bronze Hull will be used for early Steam Production and 2 Steam Machines: Alloy Smelter and Steam Furnace.
Clay is produced by throwing Stone Dust in a Mana Pool.
Bricks are made using a Wooden Form and clay, I know it's that simple. One slight snag is that laying bricks is hard, don't expect the bowl of water not to break.
Now you have an unlimited supply of dirt, you should probably make a farm with it. craft a flint hoe from gt and place the farm next to the water source you have on your island.
This boiler runs on Liquid Lava and Creosote Oil. Good if you have an excess of Creosote Oil or want to use Lava to produce steam.

Steam Solar Boilers can't be made yet. They produce steam using the power of the Sun!
You can make these once you get a couple LV Machines.

This is the first boiler you can use. 
It produces 6L/t of steam.
Don't forget to keep if full or it will explode :D
To transport steam this early on you'll have to use bronze fluid pipes. make sure you connect the fluid pipes to the target container with a gregtech wrench.
The Rain collector is the only way to get water at this point in the game. It will slowly accumulate water store in its internal tank. Might want a tank to store water.
You can now make a bucket out of Iron and move fluids instead of that primative bowl.

Water isn't infinite in this anywhere, not even river biomes so try not to remove the only block of water before you get a Rain Collector. If you do somehow remove your only block of water here Ill give you a new one. Can only be claimed once every 30 minutes.
Sand can now be obtained through the Forge hammer you have.
The ULV Robot Arm is Just a Glorified Conveyer. It allows you to limit the amount of items stored in a container.
The ULV Piston is a crafting component used for the ULV Robot Arm
ULV Motor Used for ULV Tier Components.

Any Gregtech pump will allow you to pump fluids outs of tanks into pipes or vise versa. the ULV Pump is a good starting point for fluid transport before LV.
You can also use these to pump water out of the rain collectors.
You are now in the Aether. Start by collecting some Aether dirt.
Now you have a Alloy Smelter its time to make some Charcoal. To do so you will need to build a multiblock, The coke oven.
Red Alloy Ingots are made by Alloy Smelting 4 Redstone dust with 1 Copper ingot.

The Primative Water pump generators Water. Combine with the fact you have Boilers that run off of water this might be a good idea, especially since water isn't infinite in this.

You can increase the water production based on what biome you build it in.
Ocean, River: 1000L/s 
Swamp: 800L/s
Jungle: 350L/s
Snowy: 300L/s
Plains, Forest: 250L/s
Taiga: 175L/s
Beach: 170L/s
Replacing the Pump Output Hatch with either ULV or LV Output Hatch will also increase water output by either 2x or 4x.
Many things you will need to begin Gregtech include some tools. Now you have Bronze you can make them!
The Basic Ingot Mold is going to be used to make ingots like Iron, Silver.
Gold is used for many things but the main thing is crafting a Basic Ingot Mold. You will need 8 ores to do this.
Steel is made in this monster, The Primative Blast Furnace. You actually need 36 Firebricks for the multiblock.
ULV Conveyers can be placed on any Gregtech machine, Item Pipe or Crate to transport items in/out of them. really usful early on.
Grinding ores too slow. Well look no further than the Steam Grinder.This multiblock processes 8 Items at onces. Now thats a lot of ores.
Now you have Steel from you PBF, Raw Rubber Dust from Slimonds/Sticky Resin and have Sulfer from the Nether, Combining them all will result in producing Rubber. Your gateway to Low Voltage Has begun.
Steel is used for low voltage machine hulls and components. I hope your making a lot of this because you'll need it.
Thermal Centrifuge is used to get extra products from refining ores.
Glass Tubes are made in the Alloy Smelter with a Ball Mold and Glass dust.
Vacuum Tube are the first tier Circuit at ULV Tier.
Red Alloy wires are a lossless energy wire at ULV Voltage. They are also used for your First LV Tier Circuit and automating the Orechid.

Simplest way to automate Mana Production is to place an Open Crate facing down to drop the fuel onto a pressure plate. Control a hopper on top to lock the hopper and your done. does waste an item every 5 minutes but your burning wood planks aren't you?
Circuit Boards are where you will place all the components to make a Electronic Circuit. They require some Sticky Resin and Wood Planks.
Fun jokes aside the Resistor is a crafting component used to make the Electronic Circuit.
Now you have the first of literally hundreds of these. Better start crafting more :D Electronic Circuits are a gateway Component to all the LV Machines and the Electric Blast Furnace.
Sugarcane can be crafted by droping a Hay Bale into the Manapool with some Mana. I hope you have a farm setup for wheat and I sugest setting up a farm for Sugar Cane.
Paper is now unlocked. You can now craft resistors and books.
To get Sticky Resin you start with Slimond dust and compress it into a Slimond. Next you smelt the Slimond in an Alloy Smelter with a Ball Mold to produce Sticky Resin.
This multiblock allows you to smelt 8 items at a time. Really good for smelting 1000+ items at once.
You have Steel, Rubber, Cables and ores. Now its time to start making some LV machines, start with crafting a LV Machine Hull.

You remember the ULV Components from the previous chapter? well all tiers of machines use different components based on the voltage tier. keep that in mind and check jei for the recipes if you get stuck.
The only way to generate power this early is through Steam. Steam Turbines will produce 1a at 32 Volts.

The Bending Machines is used to make Plates at a ratio of 1 Ingot to 1 Plate. 
Really important for future endeavours.
Canning Machine allows you to make Batterys.
The Centrifuges spins things so fast you get bonus outputs for certain recipes in it.

The Basic Exstractor extracts fluids from ingots.
This will be needed once you get a Circuit Assembler.
This Alloy Smelter does the same as the Steam Alloy Smelter but runs on Energy.
Chemical Reactors are your gateway to chemistry but for now you can use this one to make Rubber.
This machine sifts purified gem ores. Then outputs 3 types of gems and purified dust.
The Arc Furnace uses Oxygen to improve the properties of metals. It will be used for production of Wrought Iron and Annealed Copper.
The Electroliser seperates dusts into there elemental components. needed for production of Oxygen.
Rubber!
The Solidifier cools fluids down to form solids.
Now you can produce Annealed Copper and Wrought iron.
Lathes can make rods from any ingot with a ratio of 1 ingot to 2 rods.
Wiremills allow you to make wires at a ratio of 1 ingot to 2 wires.
The Assembling Machine can create Circuit Boards, Vacuum Tubes and Resistors more efficiently.

Batterys have 3 Tiers, Sodium, Cadmium and Lithium.
Sodium stores 80,000 EU (Worse)
Cadmium stores 100,000 EU (Middle Ground)
Lithium stores 120,000 EU (Best)
Hint: Lithium dust comes from thermal centrifuging Spodumene.
Battery alloy is needed to craft Batterys.

Dilute Mana Pool stores 1% of the mana compared to the mana pool.
Got to start somewhere though.
The Mixer mixes things. no suprise there xD

High pressure steam boilers produce 15L/t of steam. 
Thats 9L/t Of steam more than the small steam solid boiler.

The Nether is full of ores and mobs. The first ore you will need is sulfur.
Place the Nether Key on the portal to unlock it.
No Description
The High Pressure Liquid Boiler produces 30L/t of Steam compare to 12L/t For the Small Liquid Boiler.

The large bronze boiler will cure your steam needs for the moment.
It produces 800L/t of steam.

If you plan on running this of coke ovens you'll need 1 output hatch, 2 inputs hatches, 1 input bus and 1 output hatch + maintance and muffler of course.

To obtain Aluminium you'll need to travel to the Twilight Forest.
Aluminium comes from Cryolite veins and needs to be smelted in the EBF but for now you just need to make a Portal to the Twilight Forest.
For the portal you will need 12 of any flowers placed on top of grass/dirt around a 2x2 of water. Next drop a Diamond in the water and wait for the portal to spawn.

Don't forget to craft and place a Twilight key on the Portal, You won't be allowed to enter if you don't :)

The Electric Blast Furnace smelts higher tier materials. Looking through jei you will find there are 8 Tiers of coils for the ebf.
Each coil tier allows more materials to be smelted and the highest tier can smelt everything.
For now you only need the ebf to be running at MV tier and cupronickel coils.

The muffler hatch needs to be on the top of this multi in the middle of heat proof casings.

maintance, input/output bus and input/output hatch can replace any heatproof casing.

Machine Maintance is a key part of Greg tech. 
These are the tools needed to preform maintance

To power 1 Large Bronze Boiler you will need 24 coke ovens.

If You build 1 Coke Oven Array with 24 Ovens Vertical or Horizontal and wall shared you will need 489 Coke Oven Bricks.

If you build 4 Coke Oven arrays, 6 Ovens Vertical or Horizontal and wall shared you will need 516 Coke Oven Bricks

If you Build 24 Coke Ovens With no wall sharing you will need 696 Coke Oven Bricks.

Hint: you can save a sizeable amount of coke oven bricks if you wall share these vertically or horizontally.

You have two options for mining 3x3 blocks. greg tech hammers or drills.
since your here in LV you might as well make a drill.
It only costs some steel, a batter and a drill tip of your choice.
Yes ores do spawn in the aether and they are used as a gateway to aluminium.

Gravitite ore is mostly found underneath of Aether islands.
Hint: Be careful mining this falling of the island would be bad and the ore floats up if blocks above it are removed.
No Description

How do you create lava? 
well to create lava you need an LV extractor but you don't have that yet so ill trade for it.
If you somehow loose the lava bucket ill trade another one in an hour.

The Alter allows the creation of Enchanted Gravitite. 
It runs of Ambrosium so I suggest collecting a few stackes of Ambrosium.
Enchanted Gravitite is a spectial material in which armor and tools can be made from it.
Zanite Isn't the best armor in the game but the full set still gives +7 armor.

Zanite gloves have 146 durability and give + 3 attack damage.
Zanite ring has 50 durability and increases mining speed for durability.
Zanite Pendant has 99 durability and also increases mining speed for durability.

All Aether equimpent including Gloves, Rings and Pendants are accessable here.
The Gloves, ring and pendant can be placed in a special interface accessable by pressing I on your keyboard.
All Armor the Aether Mod Has to offer.
Gravitite gloves have 322 durability and give + 3 attack damage.
a full set of Gravitite armor gives 20 armor and 8 armor toughness.
No Description
No Description

You might have notised you can't place torches in the Aether.
The substitute for them is Ambrosium Torches.

Skyroot Trees give Skyroot planks.
Skyroot Planks are needed for the Alter.
Golden Skyroot trees yeild Gold dust as a chance output and Skyroot planks when sent through a cutting machine.

Manasteel is a magical metal that requires some Mana and a Steel ingot to craft.
Start by dropping a Steel ingot in a Dilute Mana Pool.

Hint: Crafting a Manasteel Block uses less Mana than Manasteel ingots do.
The Mana pool will take you to the Aether to collect Gravitite and Zanite.
Runic alter creates Runes which are used in many higher tier flowers and items from Botania.
A monster farm is probably a good idea since you'll need string for a few recipes including the Animal trap and crafting Bait.

If your having trouble getting animals maybe a ground trap is a good idea.
The Ground trap requires any type of bait accept for fish bait and produces animal drops including eggs.
betterquesting:10.name:8: Turn another page at the Animal Bar

betterquesting:10.desc:8: The Market block sells every type of seed item for emeralds, Should help with the food situation.

This is the starting chapter. Your journey awaits.
Nights are very dangerous in early game.
If you find them to hard just dig a hole and hide till its day.

Extruders allow the creation of items like small gears easier than before.
Extruders also allow you to create blaze rods from carbon and sulfur rods.
No Description

Iron III Chloride is a chemical added by Greg Tech. 
Its main use is Circuit Board production.
Gallium comes from centrifuging Purifed Sphallerite dust.
The ore Washing Plant is how you get Purifed crushed ores and can even be used to wash dusts quickly.

Cobaltite is processed in the EBF for Cobalt Arsenide and Sulfur Dioxide gas.
Realgar is processed in the EBF for Arsenic Ingots and Sulfur Dioxide gas.
Gallium Arsenide. Crafting Component for Diodes. Made by smelting Gallium and Arsenic dust in an EBF.
This flower loves oil. So much, in fact if you give it oil it produces mana and a decent rate.
This is how you make Yummy Terrasteel.
Terrasteel can be made into Gregtech Tools and is used to get a portal to Alfheim.

Sadly you can't go through it but you can throw items in it. The lovely elfs will trade certain items. 
Be careful though since the elfs are greedy and any item thrown in it they will take.

Hint: The mana pools need to be half full of mana for this to activate.
Faster Mana spreader shoots more dense Mana bursts into a Mana pool.
Yes, nothing special. Just collect the wood during the day ok.
Gravel will be required to make your first tools.
You are not restricted to Greg Tech tools so I can only suggest making a Greg Tech axe. It will chop entire trees down at once.
These are the ores to expect in a Banded Iron vein in the Nether.
Wool will be required to make a bed.
Using the wool you have collected you can now make a bed.
Nothing special here, just a crafting table and how to craft one.

Greg Tech adds its own crafting tools and are required to make any gt machines.
These tools can be made of most Greg Tech materials so for now make them out of Iron or Bronze.

Spice of life is quite a fun mod. 
If you eat a food type over and over its food value will drop.
To keep food values at there best you need to eat different types of food.
There are hundreds of food types for you to choose from, At least that helps.
This book I give you will show you the foods you haven't eaten.

Sugarcane will be later used for paper and the wheat can be used for bread.

Hint: If you can't find a Village, Break Tall grass for a chance at getting carrots, melons, potatos and pumpkins.
Paper is crafted with a soft mallet and 3 chad.
A Furnace is what you will need to start making some ingots.
A bucket is required to pickup pretty much every fluid.

Bronze is a metal alloy with a ratio of 3 parts Copper 1 part Tin. 
Its also your gateway to making your first steam machines.
Sulfur is needed for Rubber Production. Collect a stack of sulfur ore since you'll need lots of rubber.
Phenolic Circuit Boards are required to make your first MV Circuit and Second LV Circuit.
Coated Circuit Boards are made in an Alloy Smelter with 1 Treated Wood Plank and 2 Sticky Resin.

Oxygen is needed in the EBF for certain recipes. 
a good source for Oxygen is electrolysing Magnetite dust for 4000mb of oxygen and 3 Iron dust. 
Electrolysing Magnetite for Oxygen isn't the only way to get oxygen, Check Jei for more recipes.
Diodes!
Glass is needed for certain Greg Tech machines incluiding the extractor. to make glass before you have a LV Mixer, it will have to be in a crafting table with quartz sand and tiny pile of flint dust.
Molds are required to craft certain materials like glass and gears easier.
You will need 400 Charcoal to make enough Wood Tar for Phenol-Formaldehyde Resin. After that you can make Wood Tar from the Pyrolysis Oven when your reach MV.
The Distillery is used for many fluid recipes that include a fluid.

Phenol can be produced inefficiently in the Distillery with Wood Tar.
More efficient recipe unlocked In MV.
To complete this quest hold any Greg Tech Super Tank/Drum with at least 400mb of Phenol in your inventory.
Formaldehyde is needed to produce Phenol-Formaldehyde Resin. The resin to create Phenolic Circuit Boards.

Ahh Finally Phenol-Formaldehyde Resin. 
Your journey to Phenolic Circuit Boards is nearly over.

Sodium hydroxide is used to make bio-diesel and Phenol-Formaldehyde Resin.

Its made with 1 bucket of hydrogen and oxygen and 1 sodium dust or through salt water in an electrolyser. Your choice :)

Hydrogen can be produced from centrifuging Brown and yellow Limonite. 
You even get some Oxygen and Iron Dust too!
Good Circuit Boards. Wow, crafting circuits are fun :D
First MV Tier Circuit. Required for MV Tier machines.
How long did it take to make this. Well now you can craft circuits much more efficiently.

Are you tired of collecting ores when they drop far away from you?
Well this item will fix that with a little bit of energy and some steel.

There are 2 other sources to generate power, Combustion and Gas.
Combustion generators run of fluids like diesel and gasoline.
Gas turbines run of gasses like Benzene and Nitro-Benzene.

Combustion Generators burn any combustable liquid whether that liquid is an oil or a solvent. 
(Cough) Bio (Cough Cough) Diesel. 
(Cough Cough) Gasoline (Cough Cough)
Gas turbine.

Aluminium is used exclusively for MV Tier machines. 
To make some you need to mine some Cryolite.
The building block for any mv tier machine.

Silicon is a important Element, Its used for the production of high tier circuits.
A really good way to create silicon dust is the electrolysis of Silicon Dioxide Dust.
No Description
Now with this Circuit Assembler you can craft the final MV tier circuit.

Now you have a MV tier mixer you can make a new alloy called Stainless Steel.
This Material is required to make HV machine Hulls.

Cupronickel is a metal alloy that consists of 1 part Copper and 1 part Nickel. 
This alloy is mainly used to make your first EBF Coils, Cupronickel and making MV Tier Components

The overworld, the dimension you start in.
To find ores in the overworld look for tiny piles of ores on the surface. They indicate there is an ore vein underneath them.
All the quests after this one shows the ores that spawn in the specified dimension.

Your third location is the Twilight Forest. Here you will find ores like Lead and Silver in higher quantities and find Cryolite ore.
All the quests after this one shows the ores that spawn in the specified dimension.

In the End you can find ores like Uranium, Thorium and Plutonium.
All the quests after this one shows the ores that spawn in the specified dimension.
These are the ores to expect in a Cassiterite vein.
These are the ores to expect in an Chalcopyrite Cassiterite vein.
These are the ores to expect in a Chalcopyrite Iron vein.
These are the ores to expect in a Limonite vein.
These are the ores to expect in a Magnetite vein.
These are the ores to expect in an apatite vein.
Coal has its own vein by which I mean Coal only spawns in this vein.
Diamond veins contain these ores.
Lapis veins contain these ores.
Lubricant veins contain these ores. The main reason to mine this vein is for Nickel from Pentlandite.
Olivine veins contain these ores.
Redstone veins contain these ores. Primary Source of Redstone and Chrome.

Salt veins contain these ores. 
Primary source of Chlorine, Sodium and Potassium.
Centrifuging impure Lepidolite dust can yeild small amounts of Lithium.
Thermal Centrifuging crushed ore purified Spodumene ore can yeild small amounts of lithium too.
Sapphire veins contain these ores.

Slimond veins contain these ores.
Rubber trees have gone extinct but the world contains a remnant of the rubber tree.
I give you Slimond!
These are the ores to expect in a Mineral Sand vein.
The only ore in an Oilsands vein is Oilsands ore.

Good Circuit Boards require Silver. 
To obtain Silver Pre-Twilight Forest you'll need to process either Lead ore in an ore washer or Gold ore in a chemical bath with mercury.
These are the ores to expect in a Beryllium vein in the Nether.
These are the ores to expect in a Certus Quartz vein in the Nether.
These are the ores to expect in a Cobaltite vein in the Nether.
These are the ores to expect in a Nether Quartz vein in the Nether.
These are the ores to expect in a Redstone vein in the Nether.
These are the ores to expect in a Saltpeter vein in the Nether.
These are the ores to expect in a Sulfer vein in the Nether.
These are the ores to expect in a Tetrahedrite vein in the Nether.
These are the ores to expect in a Topaz vein in the Nether.

Mixing Chemicals with MV Power

You might be at the point where you cant be bothered to collect fluids manualy anymore.
Well if you do feel that way you can make a pump to pump fluids for you.

With your new found pump you can pump oil from oil wells. 
Better start Pumping.

Sulfuric Naptha is the first step to polyethylene. 
First Distil oil in the Distillery with a Programmed Circuit set to 3 to produce Sulfuric Naptha.

To De-Sulfurise the Naptha, you will need to send it through a Chemical Reactor with some Hydrogen. 

Hint: You can recycle the Hydrogen Sulfide in an Electrolyser to produce your hydrogen back!

To start cracking Naptha you need to set a Chemical Reactor to circuit 3 and pump in Steam and your Naptha. This isn't the most efficent way to Crack oils but before the Cracking Unit there is no other way.
Ethylene is a pre-cursor to Polyethylene. To produce Ethylene put you Severly-Steam Cracked Naptha in a Distillery with circuit 10 to produce Ethylene.

Polyethylene! Used for advanced electronics and machine hull production.
Will be used later to produce SMD Components.

Check jei for where ores spawn.
Most ores have a surface rock listed in jei so look for them too.
betterquesting:10.name:8: Fantastical Ores and where to find them

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Time to upgrade the energy input hatches for your EBF.
This will unlock materials for HV machines.

The Freezer cools down materials, Including some Greg Tech Hot Ingots.
This chapter you will guide you through MV tier machines,
An introduction to Greg Tech Steam Machines.
This chapter you will start to produce energy and begin mining your first ores.
All Multiblocks are in this quest chapter.
This chapter is here to guide you through the Aether and start collecting some ores.
for all your armor and equipment needs.
Botania is a "magic" mod that adds loads of flowers and the ability to craft using mana.
Open chapter to begin your journey.
This Chapter will guide you through forestry machines and farming.
